article.headline: Boise St. 70, Colorado St. 69
article.story: BOISE, Idaho -- Derrick Marks dribbled the length of the court for the winning basket with less than a second remaining to give Boise State a dramatic 70-69 victory over Colorado State on Wednesday night. Marks sped up the court, split two Colorado State defenders and kissed the ball off the glass to give the Broncos (12-12, 2-7 Mountain West) their second consecutive victory. Wes Eikmeier scored 21 of his career-high 30 points in the second half for Colorado State (15-9, 4-5), which lost its eighth straight conference road game dating back to last season. Kenny Buckner scored a career-best 20 points for Boise State. The Broncos led 64-56 after Drew Wiley drained a 3-pointer with 4:42 remaining, but Colorado State rallied with 11 consecutive points to take a 67-64 lead.
